  <input type="number" id="fnN" value="15" style="width:70px;font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.8rem;padding:0.2rem 0.4rem;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--border-r);">
  <span style="font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--muted);">x:</span>
  <input type="number" id="fnX" value="7" style="width:70px;font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.8rem;padding:0.2rem 0.4rem;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--border-r);">
  <button class="btn sm" onclick="runFactor()">Trace Algorithm</button>
</div>
<div id="factorResult" style="font-family:'IBM Plex Mono',monospace;font-size:0.78rem;color:var(--ink2);margin-top:0.5rem;min-height:2rem;line-height:1.8;"></div>

<!-- Exercises -->
<div class="ex-block">
  <div class="ex-header"><span class="ex-tag">Ex 2.1</span><span class="ex-title">Why is step ③ needed?</span></div>
  <div class="ex-body">
    <p>Step ③ says: if r is odd, restart. Why can't we use an odd r in step ④?</p>
  </div>
  <div class="answer-area">
    <div class="answer-row">
      <input class="answer-input" id="a21" placeholder="..." style="width:280px;">
      <button class="btn sm" onclick="chkContains('a21',['r/2','half','integer','x^(r/2'],'fb21')">Check</button>
      <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHint('h21')">show hint</button>
    </div>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h21">Because x<sup>(r/2)</sup> needs to be an integer. If r is odd, r/2 is not an integer and x<sup>(r/2)</sup> mod n is undefined. We need r to be even so that x<sup>(r/2)</sup> ∈ ℤ.</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="fb21"></div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="ex-block">
  <div class="ex-header"><span class="ex-tag">Ex 2.2</span><span class="ex-title">Verify the factoring of 15</span></div>
  <div class="ex-body">
    <p>For n=15 and x=7: the order is r=4 (meaning 7<sup>4</sup> mod 15 = 1). Compute gcd(7²−1, 15) = gcd(48, 15). What factor do you get?</p>
  </div>
  <div class="answer-area">
    <div class="answer-row">
      <span class="ans-label">gcd(48,15) =</span>
      <input class="answer-input" id="a22" placeholder="?" style="width:80px;">
      <button class="btn sm" onclick="chk('a22','3','fb22')">Check</button>
      <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHint('h22')">show hint</button>
    </div>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h22">48 = 3×16, 15 = 3×5. gcd(48,15) = 3. And gcd(50,15) = 5. So factors of 15 are 3 and 5. ✓</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="fb22"></div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

